text: I see, you went to a school in the middle of the city, huh?
You, a hikikomori, actually went to a place with lots of people.
I might as well say that my hikikomori condition has been cured.
Now you should be fine going outside by yourself, huh?
Oh yeah, I'm not hikikomori anymore!
You know the project is due today, right?
Yup! I got it right here!
It looks like your work is pretty amateurish actually.
Damn it! Is it a trap?!
So, it was them behind this all along.
I'm the victim of a conspiracy plotted by the Nihon Hikikomori Kyokai!
Sorry to have you do this every day.
After all, you've been paying for my services.
People always say that summer colds take a long time to get over,
but you really have been sick for a long time.
It's like, my body still feels sluggish.
At first, I thought your hikikomori condition got worse.
Remember, I went to your school the other day by myself.
This is a conspiracy plotted by the Nihon Hikikomori Kyokai!
Ever since I visited Yamazaki's school,
my hikikomori condition has gotten much worse.
I don't want to see anyone.
I don't even want to answer my cell phone.
I don't want to do anything.
I don't want to even live.
But dying is a pain in the ass too.
I wish I could just disappear.
I wonder what would have happened to me if Yamazaki had never come to check on me?
I just lied to Yamazaki saying I had a summer cold.
But I'm sure he's going to find out that's a lie sooner or later.
What the hell am I supposed to do now?
Fight, Sato! Fight against the enemy's conspiracy!
You must fight against the conspiracy plotted by the Nihon Hikikomori Kyokai!
Fight against them? But I don't have any weapons.
But I don't have love or courage.
A phone call! A phone call!
Huh? This is certainly unusual. Telephone's calling you!
A phone call! A phone call!
I wonder if there's been some kind of accident or something?
A phone call! A phone call!
Sorry, I'm not available to take your call.
Please leave a message after the beep.
If you wish to send me a fax, please press your send button now.
I have some business in Tokyo, so I'm coming up there.
I was thinking I should drop by and see you while I'm there.
And we could discuss your future plans and stuff then too.
Is she planning to make me move back home?!
After everything I've done to move to Tokyo?!
I'd just be a loser if I move back home!
If you're home, answer the phone, all right?
Oh, I just came back in.
Really? Then I guess you still haven't checked your message,
but my class reunion is coming up on Saturday.
And it looks like I'll have some free time the day before the reunion,
so I want to see you and discuss some things!
You can't just keep on wasting your time doing nothing in Tokyo forever, you know.
Isn't it time for you to come back home and get a job down here?
Besides you'll never be able to get married at this rate.
Actually, I've already found a job.
It's a small software company, but I've been writing scripts and stuff for them.
And I haven't told you this,
but there's someone I'm considering getting married to as well.
So, I've pretty much decided on settling down here in Tokyo.
I've been so worried about you.
But good, you've got a job now and you're getting married.
Well, the marriage part isn't gonna happen anytime soon.
You see, they don't pay you a whole lot when you start a new job.
That's all right! Just knowing that you've got a girlfriend is such a relief!
You have to let me meet her when I come to Tokyo, all right?
Okay, then I'll call you again with the flight information and stuff!
Don't buy into it so easily.
Can't you tell it's a lie?
Is this Mr. Tatsuhiro Sato's residence?
So, this is the right number then.
Hey, I've been worried about you.
You haven't shown up for counseling or answered your cell phone.
Wait, I have a really good reason for this whole thing!
First of all, I have a more important thing to worry about right now!
Well, I just found out that my mother is coming to Tokyo.
So, you told her you've got a job at a promising company
and a girlfriend who's going to marry you.
There are limits to how much you should make up.
What was I supposed to do?!
She was planning to drag me back home unless I told her stuff like that!
I have two more days before she comes.
I have to come up with a way to fool her before that!
I guess I have no choice, do I, Sato?
I don't mind pretending to be your girlfriend for a day if you want me to.
I just have to ask Yamazaki!
Ya-Yamazaki is going to be your girlfriend?!
You can't do that! No way!
I have no time to waste! I'm gonna ask Yamazaki right now!
A company! We're gonna make a company, Yamazaki!
you can establish a company with as little as one yen capital these days!
If we establish a company, I can fool my mother!
Wait, we were gonna make the world's preeminent game company to begin with anyway!
It's just that our plan has been accelerated a little!
We're are going to proudly bring our own brand to the game industry, Yamazaki!
That sounds great! Let's do it!
First, let's pick a company name!
Why don't we take "Sa" from Sato and '"Yama" from Yamazaki
and call it "Sayama Company"! How's that?
But then it sounds like a person named Sayama founded the company.
Okay, for now let's say that our company name is '"Y.S. Company."
I'm not happy with the name either, so let's change it once we become big!
Next up is the company logo!
Since it's "Y.S.", how about something like this?
Hey, it looks like a logo on the baseball cap for some baseball team.
I mean, for now, just for now.
Company song! Company song! Company song for Y.S.!
but I've already told my mother that I found a job, so...
I've got a job title that's perfect for you!
That explains your current status in on simple word, doesn't it?
I'm working hard so that she doesn't find out that's what I am, you jerk!
First of all, NEET isn't a business title!
The reception desk is the face of the company!
Therefore, we're going to ask her to be the receptionist for our company!
Are you really going to show this to your mother?
what we need is for it to appear as though our company is legit, right?
Because you don't really want to bring her to this room.
I think she'll be convinced if I show this business card to her.
How are you going to fool her about the girlfriend who's going to marry you?
If you want me to, I can pretend to be your girlfriend for a day.
I'm sure Senpai will help me out on this one if I explain the situation!
Besides, it's possible that something intended as a lie could come true too!
I'm sorry, but I already have plans.
Yeah, I have an appointment with my friend.
Now that it's come to this, I guess I'll have Yamazaki dress in drag.
Nice to meet you, Mother! I'm Kaoru Yamazaki!
I won't be able to take it.
I can do it for you, you know,
Say, do we really have to do this?
Look, when you lie, it's written all over your face.
If we don't have at least one real date beforehand, she'll be able to tell you're lying right away.
But if I go to some place with a bunch of people, the same thing might happen to me again.
If we're together, I'm sure you'll be fine.
I guess this is what a so-called "normal relationship" is.
We should've made it more official and dated each other back then, huh?
Wanna try walking arm in arm?
We look more like a real couple that way.
Is she coming on to me?!
Is this lie turning into the truth?!
Next time will be the real deal, huh?
You'd better clean up your apartment, or your mother will be shocked.
If we're going to pretend to be a couple,
won't it be a problem if we don't know more about each other?
Your name is about the only thing I know about you, you know.
Actually, I know you very well, Sato.
Name, Tatsuhiro Sato. Date of birth, January 28th, Aquarius.
Blood type A. You were born in Hokkaido.
Oh yeah, and recently you've gotten into gal games and collecting pictures of a "graphic" nature.
The last place you attended school was at Heisei Bunka University, a private school,
Your father's name is Tatsuo. Mother's name is Shizue.
Why do you know so much about me?
Yeah, I have a good memory.
Is this Mr. Tatsuhiro Sato's residence?
Now that I think about it...
Why does she knows the phone number to my apartment?
The only people I've given that number to are my parents back home.
You haven't told me anything about yourself yet.
It'll be a problem if I don't know anything about you when my mother asks me, won't it?
Okay, I'll tell you, but you have to memorize it.
First, I'll tell you about my family tree.
My grandfather is French and his name is Georges Brufelles.
My grandmother is a Japanese prima donna!
They met at Port Moresby and fell in love. They came back to Japan and got married.
Then my mother was born and she got married to my father, an elite businessman.
Then I was born, but now I live with my relatives due to unavoidable familial circumstances.
Then what is my grandfather's name?
Jeez, you have to remember it by tomorrow. That's your homework!
Hey, it's obviously a lie! What does she mean, he's French?!
Arrive at Haneda Airport 12:35 PM.\NArrival gate 2.\NPick me up at the airport.\N- Mom.
Pick me up at the airport. Mom.
I can't believe a cute girl like her will be my daughter-in-law!
